HEADWORD: Penetrancy
<hw>Pen"e*tran*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
penetrant; power of entering or piercing; penetrating power or quality;
<as>as, the <ex>penetrancy</ex> of subtile effluvia</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penetrant</ent>⟦br⟧
